Question
One-line Answer
SG vs NACL
SG is stateful and instance-level, NACL is stateless and subnet-level.
IGW vs NAT Gateway
IGW allows public internet access, NAT allows private instances to access internet outbound.
ALB vs NLB
ALB works at Layer 7, NLB works at Layer 

4.
Multi-AZ vs Read Replica
Multi-AZ is for HA, Read Replica is for read scaling.
CloudWatch vs CloudTrail
CloudWatch monitors performance, CloudTrail records API activity.
IAM User vs Role
User is permanent identity, role gives temporary permissions.
S3 vs EBS
S3 is object storage, EBS is block storage.
Vertical vs Horizontal Scaling
Vertical means bigger server, horizontal means more servers.
RTO vs RPO
RTO is recovery time, RPO is acceptable data loss.
Public vs Private Subnet
Public subnet has route to IGW, private subnet does not. 
